properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued February 12 at 1:36PM MST until February 13 at 3:00AM MST by NWS Cheyenne WY
properties.description:
...Slick Roads and Low Visibility Likely During Evening Commute
and Tonight on I-80 Summit...

* WHAT...Snow expected. Total snow accumulations of up to two
inches.

* WHERE...Interstate 80 between Laramie and Cheyenne, specifically
on the I-80 Summit.

* WHEN...Until 3 AM MST Thursday.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions and reductions to
visibility. The hazardous conditions could impact the evening
commute.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 3 AM MST THURSDAY
